candidates.title: Add tls support for pgstac
candidates.body:
## Closes

- #375 

## Description
This change moves the default TLS connection from `NoTls` to a configurable struct provided by a small TLS wrapper package from the `tokio_postgres` ecosystem. This makes rudimentary TLS the default encryption which is an approach taken by the widely used `sqlx` library.

I considered using generics, but things got hairy quite quickly. We could open up the `new` method into the public API or add a `From` implementation to make it possible for users to use their own configurations for the TLS struct.

I'd be open to adding a couple of extra tests if you could advise where.
